50|$|In 1996, the Center for Constitutional Rights sued Shell for its {{complicity}} {{in human rights}} abuses against the <b>Ogoni</b> <b>people,</b> such as colluding with the Nigerian government {{to bring about the}} arrest and execution of the Ogoni Nine. In June 2009, on the eve of trial, the parties agreed to a settlement providing a total of $15.5 million to compensate the plaintiffs, establish a trust {{for the benefit of the}} <b>Ogoni</b> <b>people,</b> and cover some of the legal costs and fees associated with the case.|$|E
